Here it is. The CMM interface is at:

```
submodules/MaterialProviders/AwsCryptographicMaterialProviders/runtimes/java/src/main/smithy-generated/
  software/amazon/cryptography/materialproviders/ICryptographicMaterialsManager.java
```

The interface:

```java
package software.amazon.cryptography.materialproviders;

public interface ICryptographicMaterialsManager {
  DecryptMaterialsOutput DecryptMaterials(DecryptMaterialsInput input);
  GetEncryptionMaterialsOutput GetEncryptionMaterials(GetEncryptionMaterialsInput input);
}
```

So in the native Java DB-ESDK, you'd call `cmm.GetEncryptionMaterials(input)` where `input` is a `GetEncryptionMaterialsInput` (from `software.amazon.cryptography.materialproviders.model`). Want me to show the input/output model classes too?

In this repository, we write code in Dafny in /Users/rishavkj/Documents/Storage/Team-Repos/aws-database-encryption-sdk-dynamodb/DynamoDbEncryption/dafny then generate it to Java, Rust and .NET. For public facing APIs, we write code in smithy model (in DynamoDbEncryption/*/Model/*.smithy) and generate it in DynamoDbEncryption/runtimes/java/src/main/smithy-generated. Read the specification for it in /Users/rishavkj/Documents/Storage/Team-Repos/aws-database-encryption-sdk-dynamodb/specification. The specification is linked to the code with comments: 

```
//= specification/dynamodb-encryption-client/ddb-get-encrypted-data-key-description.md#behavior
//# - If the input is an encrypted DynamoDB item, it MUST attempt to extract "aws_dbe_head" attribute from the DynamoDB item to get the binary header.
```
